[
    {
        "text": "Violence",
        "start": 0.315,
        "duration": 0.899
    },
    {
        "text": "and war.",
        "start": 1.214,
        "duration": 1.183
    },
    {
        "text": "The insane brutality of ISIS continues,",
        "start": 2.397,
        "duration": 2.831
    },
    {
        "text": "the Russians are invading Ukraine,",
        "start": 5.228,
        "duration": 2.086
    },
    {
        "text": "and the Palestinians and Israelis",
        "start": 7.314,
        "duration": 1.578
    },
    {
        "text": "continue to slug it out.",
        "start": 8.892,
        "duration": 1.598
    },
    {
        "text": "Does that make you feel gloomy?",
        "start": 10.49,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "Well",
        "start": 12.745,
        "duration": 0.836
    },
    {
        "text": "don't.",
        "start": 13.581,
        "duration": 0.72
    },
    {
        "text": "Because if you look at the numbers",
        "start": 14.301,
        "duration": 1.659
    },
    {
        "text": "war actually seems",
        "start": 15.96,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": "to be going out of fashion,",
        "start": 17.22,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "while the global population",
        "start": 18.54,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "is at an all time high.",
        "start": 20.06,
        "duration": 1.998
    },
    {
        "text": "It seems that we live",
        "start": 22.058,
        "duration": 1.312
    },
    {
        "text": "in the most peaceful period",
        "start": 23.37,
        "duration": 1.333
    },
    {
        "text": "in human history.",
        "start": 24.703,
        "duration": 1.361
    },
    {
        "text": "How is this possible?",
        "start": 26.064,
        "duration": 1.606
    },
    {
        "text": "(music)",
        "start": 27.67,
        "duration": 4.713
    },
    {
        "text": "As of September 2014,",
        "start": 34.065,
        "duration": 1.964
    },
    {
        "text": "there were 4 conflicts going on",
        "start": 36.029,
        "duration": 1.491
    },
    {
        "text": "in the world that'd caused at least",
        "start": 37.52,
        "duration": 1.669
    },
    {
        "text": "10,000 people to die since January 2013.",
        "start": 39.189,
        "duration": 3.044
    },
    {
        "text": "9 conflicts that killed",
        "start": 42.233,
        "duration": 1.449
    },
    {
        "text": "more than 1,000 people",
        "start": 43.682,
        "duration": 1.434
    },
    {
        "text": "and 13 that killed",
        "start": 45.116,
        "duration": 1.431
    },
    {
        "text": "more than 100 since January 2013.",
        "start": 46.547,
        "duration": 3.008
    },
    {
        "text": "Not really peaceful,",
        "start": 49.555,
        "duration": 1.611
    },
    {
        "text": "but consider this:",
        "start": 51.166,
        "duration": 1.18
    },
    {
        "text": "of all the conflicts going on",
        "start": 52.346,
        "duration": 1.426
    },
    {
        "text": "none is an active war between countries.",
        "start": 53.772,
        "duration": 2.71
    },
    {
        "text": "They are either civil wars",
        "start": 56.482,
        "duration": 1.957
    },
    {
        "text": "or local conflicts.",
        "start": 58.439,
        "duration": 1.64
    },
    {
        "text": "Although civil wars are terrible",
        "start": 60.084,
        "duration": 1.729
    },
    {
        "text": "and cause huge suffering,",
        "start": 61.813,
        "duration": 1.659
    },
    {
        "text": "their impact is usually way smaller",
        "start": 63.472,
        "duration": 1.79
    },
    {
        "text": "than a war between nations or empires.",
        "start": 65.262,
        "duration": 2.505
    },
    {
        "text": "When two nations engage in war,",
        "start": 67.767,
        "duration": 2.422
    },
    {
        "text": "they can mobilise much bigger forces,",
        "start": 70.189,
        "duration": 2.354
    },
    {
        "text": "have access to all of the state's",
        "start": 72.543,
        "duration": 2.177
    },
    {
        "text": "resources and logistics and",
        "start": 74.72,
        "duration": 2.135
    },
    {
        "text": "almost all of the population.",
        "start": 76.855,
        "duration": 2.655
    },
    {
        "text": "So why have we transitioned from",
        "start": 79.51,
        "duration": 1.866
    },
    {
        "text": "wars between nation states",
        "start": 81.376,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "wars between nation states",
        "start": 83.326,
        "duration": 1.624
    },
    {
        "text": "A lot of it is to do with",
        "start": 84.95,
        "duration": 1.823
    },
    {
        "text": "colonialism and the cold war.",
        "start": 86.773,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "When the cold war ended, a major driver of",
        "start": 89.213,
        "duration": 2.554
    },
    {
        "text": "armed conflicts vanished too.",
        "start": 91.767,
        "duration": 1.82
    },
    {
        "text": "But the break up of the",
        "start": 93.587,
        "duration": 1.117
    },
    {
        "text": "communist dictatorships",
        "start": 94.704,
        "duration": 1.368
    },
    {
        "text": "revealed new or old tensions",
        "start": 96.072,
        "duration": 2.017
    },
    {
        "text": "and brought new conflicts",
        "start": 98.089,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "in the now freed states",
        "start": 99.84,
        "duration": 1.309
    },
    {
        "text": "which often resulted in civil war.",
        "start": 101.149,
        "duration": 2.721
    },
    {
        "text": "Much more importantly,",
        "start": 103.87,
        "duration": 1.862
    },
    {
        "text": "in 1945,",
        "start": 105.732,
        "duration": 1.675
    },
    {
        "text": "nearly all of Africa, much of Asia,",
        "start": 107.407,
        "duration": 2.38
    },
    {
        "text": "and parts of Latin America",
        "start": 109.787,
        "duration": 1.558
    },
    {
        "text": "were under colonial rule.",
        "start": 111.345,
        "duration": 1.726
    },
    {
        "text": "By 1990,",
        "start": 113.071,
        "duration": 1.228
    },
    {
        "text": "all but a few islands were independent.",
        "start": 114.299,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "But wait.",
        "start": 117.419,
        "duration": 0.975
    },
    {
        "text": "Couldn't you argue that what today's",
        "start": 118.394,
        "duration": 1.657
    },
    {
        "text": "multinational corporations",
        "start": 120.051,
        "duration": 1.412
    },
    {
        "text": "are doing in the third world",
        "start": 121.463,
        "duration": 1.233
    },
    {
        "text": "is just as bad as colonialism?",
        "start": 122.696,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's look at Congo.",
        "start": 125.036,
        "duration": 1.653
    },
    {
        "text": "It was established as a colony in 1885",
        "start": 126.689,
        "duration": 2.407
    },
    {
        "text": "by the Belgium king.",
        "start": 129.096,
        "duration": 1.393
    },
    {
        "text": "An area 80 times the size of Belgium.",
        "start": 130.489,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "Violence committed against",
        "start": 133.369,
        "duration": 1.567
    },
    {
        "text": "the indigenous Congolese",
        "start": 134.936,
        "duration": 1.271
    },
    {
        "text": "and the ruthless system of",
        "start": 136.207,
        "duration": 1.336
    },
    {
        "text": "economic exploitation",
        "start": 137.543,
        "duration": 1.401
    },
    {
        "text": "had killed about half of the population",
        "start": 138.944,
        "duration": 2.45
    },
    {
        "text": "by 1908.",
        "start": 141.394,
        "duration": 1.979
    },
    {
        "text": "About 10 million Congolese were executed",
        "start": 143.373,
        "duration": 2.92
    },
    {
        "text": "or starved to death.",
        "start": 146.298,
        "duration": 1.671
    },
    {
        "text": "Millions were mutilated and traumatised.",
        "start": 147.969,
        "duration": 3.019
    },
    {
        "text": "The economic exploitation of the Congo",
        "start": 150.988,
        "duration": 2.478
    },
    {
        "text": "remained the top priority",
        "start": 153.466,
        "duration": 1.808
    },
    {
        "text": "and forced labor never really ceased",
        "start": 155.274,
        "duration": 2.263
    },
    {
        "text": "completely until the end of Belgium rule",
        "start": 157.537,
        "duration": 2.504
    },
    {
        "text": "in 1960.",
        "start": 160.041,
        "duration": 1.241
    },
    {
        "text": "Which is not really that long ago.",
        "start": 161.282,
        "duration": 2.921
    },
    {
        "text": "So, no.",
        "start": 164.203,
        "duration": 1.174
    },
    {
        "text": "Colonialism was much worse than",
        "start": 165.377,
        "duration": 1.933
    },
    {
        "text": "vulture capitalism is today",
        "start": 167.31,
        "duration": 1.891
    },
    {
        "text": "and it ended just two generations ago.",
        "start": 169.201,
        "duration": 2.673
    },
    {
        "text": "Most of the conflicts",
        "start": 171.874,
        "duration": 1.287
    },
    {
        "text": "that are going on right now",
        "start": 173.161,
        "duration": 1.39
    },
    {
        "text": "are in areas that 60 years ago",
        "start": 174.551,
        "duration": 2.155
    },
    {
        "text": "were under foreign control.",
        "start": 176.706,
        "duration": 2.345
    },
    {
        "text": "But things are getting better.",
        "start": 179.051,
        "duration": 1.825
    },
    {
        "text": "Until 1989,",
        "start": 180.876,
        "duration": 1.851
    },
    {
        "text": "victory for one side in a civil war",
        "start": 182.727,
        "duration": 1.882
    },
    {
        "text": "was common",
        "start": 184.609,
        "duration": 0.762
    },
    {
        "text": "while nowadays victories are much rarer.",
        "start": 185.371,
        "duration": 2.881
    },
    {
        "text": "At the same time,",
        "start": 188.252,
        "duration": 1.484
    },
    {
        "text": "negotiated endings have jumped from 10%",
        "start": 189.736,
        "duration": 2.253
    },
    {
        "text": "to almost 40%.",
        "start": 191.989,
        "duration": 1.568
    },
    {
        "text": "What about the rest of the world?",
        "start": 193.557,
        "duration": 2.167
    },
    {
        "text": "Why have nation states",
        "start": 195.724,
        "duration": 1.561
    },
    {
        "text": "stopped attacking each other?",
        "start": 197.285,
        "duration": 1.628
    },
    {
        "text": "There are 4 major reasons:",
        "start": 198.913,
        "duration": 2.174
    },
    {
        "text": "One.",
        "start": 201.087,
        "duration": 0.706
    },
    {
        "text": "Democratisation.",
        "start": 201.793,
        "duration": 1.39
    },
    {
        "text": "The steady development",
        "start": 203.183,
        "duration": 1.105
    },
    {
        "text": "from autocracy to democracy.",
        "start": 204.288,
        "duration": 2.283
    },
    {
        "text": "Democracies hardly ever fight each other.",
        "start": 206.571,
        "duration": 2.671
    },
    {
        "text": "Of all the state against state wars",
        "start": 209.242,
        "duration": 2.183
    },
    {
        "text": "fought since 1900, only a minority",
        "start": 211.425,
        "duration": 2.876
    },
    {
        "text": "were fought between democracies.",
        "start": 214.301,
        "duration": 2.118
    },
    {
        "text": "Two.",
        "start": 216.419,
        "duration": 0.83
    },
    {
        "text": "Globalisation.",
        "start": 217.249,
        "duration": 1.212
    },
    {
        "text": "War is just not as effective at achieving",
        "start": 218.461,
        "duration": 2.917
    },
    {
        "text": "economic goals as it used to be.",
        "start": 221.378,
        "duration": 2.502
    },
    {
        "text": "Today it's almost always cheaper",
        "start": 223.88,
        "duration": 2.146
    },
    {
        "text": "to buy resources on the global market",
        "start": 226.026,
        "duration": 1.997
    },
    {
        "text": "than to cease them by force.",
        "start": 228.023,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "People from other nations are",
        "start": 230.033,
        "duration": 1.779
    },
    {
        "text": "more valuable to us alive than dead.",
        "start": 231.812,
        "duration": 2.74
    },
    {
        "text": "Which, overall, is a pretty new concept.",
        "start": 234.552,
        "duration": 3.008
    },
    {
        "text": "Three.",
        "start": 237.56,
        "duration": 1.064
    },
    {
        "text": "War is so 20th century.",
        "start": 238.624,
        "duration": 2.794
    },
    {
        "text": "Until World War I, warfare was seen as an",
        "start": 241.418,
        "duration": 3.23
    },
    {
        "text": "inevitable part of the human experience",
        "start": 244.649,
        "duration": 2.235
    },
    {
        "text": "and as a valuable tool which you could use",
        "start": 246.884,
        "duration": 2.727
    },
    {
        "text": "to achieve goals when diplomacy",
        "start": 249.611,
        "duration": 1.624
    },
    {
        "text": "hit a brick wall.",
        "start": 251.235,
        "duration": 1.522
    },
    {
        "text": "Today we have rules that declare acts of",
        "start": 252.757,
        "duration": 1.967
    },
    {
        "text": "aggression illegal and stipulate that",
        "start": 254.724,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "armed forces is only justified in",
        "start": 256.967,
        "duration": 1.985
    },
    {
        "text": "self-defence or with the authority of the",
        "start": 258.952,
        "duration": 2.342
    },
    {
        "text": "UN Security Council.",
        "start": 261.294,
        "duration": 1.838
    },
    {
        "text": "These rules are still broken but today",
        "start": 263.132,
        "duration": 2.673
    },
    {
        "text": "it's harder to do so without sparking",
        "start": 265.805,
        "duration": 2.433
    },
    {
        "text": "oppositions and disapproval.",
        "start": 268.238,
        "duration": 2.111
    },
    {
        "text": "Also, we have an international court for",
        "start": 270.349,
        "duration": 2.301
    },
    {
        "text": "war crimes in The Hague.",
        "start": 272.65,
        "duration": 1.647
    },
    {
        "text": "And that's a very recent innovation.",
        "start": 274.297,
        "duration": 3.026
    },
    {
        "text": "Four.",
        "start": 277.323,
        "duration": 0.99
    },
    {
        "text": "Borders are mostly fixed now.",
        "start": 278.318,
        "duration": 2.398
    },
    {
        "text": "After World War II,",
        "start": 280.716,
        "duration": 1.536
    },
    {
        "text": "territorial wars generally stopped",
        "start": 282.252,
        "duration": 2.2
    },
    {
        "text": "when most countries pledged to accept",
        "start": 284.468,
        "duration": 1.913
    },
    {
        "text": "international borders",
        "start": 286.381,
        "duration": 1.06
    },
    {
        "text": "and respect other nations autonomy.",
        "start": 287.45,
        "duration": 2.569
    },
    {
        "text": "But is all of this just an anomaly",
        "start": 290.019,
        "duration": 2.026
    },
    {
        "text": "or are we on the road to lasting peace?",
        "start": 292.045,
        "duration": 2.449
    },
    {
        "text": "Truth is",
        "start": 294.494,
        "duration": 0.8
    },
    {
        "text": "we don't know yet.",
        "start": 295.294,
        "duration": 1.43
    },
    {
        "text": "We need a big enough sample to rule out",
        "start": 296.724,
        "duration": 1.626
    },
    {
        "text": "the historical average, which is about",
        "start": 298.35,
        "duration": 1.677
    },
    {
        "text": "one or two big wars per century.",
        "start": 300.027,
        "duration": 1.902
    },
    {
        "text": "We just haven't had enough time since",
        "start": 301.929,
        "duration": 1.73
    },
    {
        "text": "World War II to rule out the possibility",
        "start": 303.659,
        "duration": 2.073
    },
    {
        "text": "that war is not going away.",
        "start": 305.732,
        "duration": 1.72
    },
    {
        "text": "If we don't have one major war",
        "start": 307.452,
        "duration": 1.716
    },
    {
        "text": "in the next 75 years,",
        "start": 309.168,
        "duration": 1.724
    },
    {
        "text": "we can be really confident",
        "start": 310.892,
        "duration": 1.503
    },
    {
        "text": "that humanity is changing.",
        "start": 312.395,
        "duration": 1.827
    },
    {
        "text": "So you see, war might be over.",
        "start": 314.222,
        "duration": 2.944
    },
    {
        "text": "Yes there are nasty conflicts",
        "start": 317.166,
        "duration": 1.734
    },
    {
        "text": "going on in many places but overall,",
        "start": 318.9,
        "duration": 2.067
    },
    {
        "text": "things are getting better.",
        "start": 320.967,
        "duration": 1.393
    },
    {
        "text": "And we can make them even better",
        "start": 322.36,
        "duration": 1.406
    },
    {
        "text": "by speaking up for peace and democracy.",
        "start": 323.766,
        "duration": 3.627
    },
    {
        "text": "Subtitles by the Amara.org community",
        "start": 343.0,
        "duration": 3.0
    }
]